#: ../../_includes/_adminpanel/mta.rst:73
msgid ""
"**Ignore**. This is the default action: simply ignore the result of the "
"test, but allow other tests to be carried out on the e-mail. Tests will "
"be executed again in case the client connects again in the future"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_adminpanel/mta.rst:78
msgid ""
"This option is useful for testing and collecting statistics without "
"blocking mail."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_adminpanel/mta.rst:81
msgid ""
"**Enforce**. The e-mail is rejected (with an SMTP 550 reply) and some of "
"the e-mail's data (helo, sender, and recipient) are logged. Other tests "
"will be carried out on the e-mail, and tests will be executed again in "
"case the client connects again in the future"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_adminpanel/mta.rst:87
msgid ""
"**Drop**. The incoming connection is immediately dropped (with an SMTP "
"521 reply). Tests will be executed again in case the client connects "
"again in the future."
msgstr ""

